                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable T</hi> 52.) I live in Bow-street, Covent-garden—the prisoner was formerly in the police-force. On the 19th of August I had a great-coat hanging up in my cupboard, by my bed-room—the closet was not locked—the prisoner absented himself from the sta<lb></lb>tion-house the night I lost the coat—I found him in Primrose-street, City, with the coat on his back—this is it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> When I took the coat I was going home to my Mend's in Norfolk—Dawson knew me, and knew my friends—I worked for Dawson—I intended to send him the coat back again.</p>
